ğŸ”¹ How to Contribute
1. Fork the repo
git fork https://github.com/Self-Defi/solana-orderflow-vaults.git

2. Clone your fork
git clone https://github.com/YOUR-USER/solana-orderflow-vaults.git
cd solana-orderflow-vaults

3. Create a feature branch
git checkout -b feature/your-improvement

4. Make changes and commit

Follow clear, descriptive commits:

âœ” feat: add tooltip UI
âœ” refactor: improve vault rendering logic
âœ” docs: clarify yield model language

5. Push and open a pull request
git push origin feature/your-improvement


Then submit a PR via GitHub.

ğŸ”¹ Pull Request Requirements

To maintain clarity and minimalism:

Explain why your change matters

Keep changes clean and focused

If UI related, include screenshots

If protocol/data related, cite source logic

We review PRs for:

clarity

maintainability

alignment with Self-Defi principles

non-custodial execution safety

